streams

Interface Function<E,F>

  • Functional Interface:
    This is a functional interface and can therefore be used as the assignment target for a lambda expression or method reference. 

    public interface Function<E,F>
    Specify an interface for a Function type to pass as argument to Stream#map. Instances of Function for types E and F represents a computation taking as input an instance of type E and returning an instance of type F.
    Version:
    0.1.3
    Author:
    hugo benichi
    See Also:
    Stream
